  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" K. Subramaniam (Died) Through LRs K.S. Balakrishnan & Ors. versus M/s Krishna Mills Pvt. Ltd. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_12_167_188','2025INSC1309'); ><font size='4'> <strong>K. SUBRAMANIAM (DIED) THROUGH LRS K.S. BALAKRISHNAN & ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>M/S KRISHNA MILLS PVT. LTD. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 12 S.C.R. 167</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1309</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006612025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : DIPANKAR DATTA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, MANMOHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the High Court was right in declining to reverse the appellate order of eviction obtained by the respondent-owner against the appellants-lessee on the ground of wilful default in payment of rent. Headnotes Tamil Nadu Control) Act, 1960 &ndash; s.10(2)(i) &ndash; Eviction on the ground of wilful default &ndash; Respondent-owner leased out properties to lessee for a monthly rent of Rs. 48,000/-, however, the lessee paid Rs.33,000/- &ndash; Rent Controller fixed a fair rent which was upheld by the appellate<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 11-11-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 2561/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_12_167_188','2025INSC1309','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'><